      <title>Illnesses you could get from exposure to flood water from Hurricane Florence</title>
      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANMembers of the public are at risk of catching illnesses from the flood water left behind by Hurricane Florence.Diarrheal diseases such as cryptosporidiosis, E.Coli or giardiasis could be caused by eating or drinking anything that have come into contact with the contaminated flood water, reports Journal-News.The different diarrheal diseases include symptoms such as diarrhea and nausea.Rashes and open wounds exposed to flood water also increase the risk of people being infected with tetanus, which is a bacterial infection that could break into the skin.Another illness people could contract by being in the flooded waters for too long is trench foot. This illness could cause pain, swelling and numbness.Stagnant flood waters is a gateway for bacteria to enter the body through any open wounds or injuries, ABC News reports.Officials are encouraging the public to try to avoid exposure to floodwaters, and to keep any open wounds as clean and as dry as possible.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Diarrheal diseases that one could get through exposure to contaminated flood water.2. Symptoms of diarrheal diseases.3. Tetanus disease is shown. 4. Trench foot disease is shown.VOICEOVER (in English): "Journal-News reports, diarrheal diseases such as cryptosporidiosis, E.Coli or giardiasis could be caused by eating or drinking anything that have come into contact with the contaminated flood water.""The different diarrheal diseases include symptoms such as diarrhea and nausea.""Rashes and open wounds exposed to flood water also increase the risk of people being infected with tetanus, which is a bacterial infection that could break into the skin.""Another illness people could get by being in the flooded waters for too long is trench foot. This illness could cause pain, swelling and numbness."SOURCES: Journal-News, ABC News, The Weather Channel https://www.journal-news.com/weather/hurricane-florence-aftermath-scary-infectious-illnesses-you-can-catch-from-floodwater/O0867RHawZ9LQit0MTUygN/https://abcnews.go.com/Health/florences-floodwaters-carry-hidden-dangers-electrocution-injury-disease/story?id=57821307https://weather.com/storms/hurricane/news/2018-09-16-florence-health-hazards-electrocution-infection-injury***]]></description>
