a levels, with storms moving more slowly, thus increased levels of precipitation and flooding." "Scientists say that for every degree the air warms, it can hold almost 4 percent more water and feeds more energy into the storm." "Climate scientists say the warmer air and water make storms stronger. Recent studies have also shown storms intensifying more rapidly than before." SOURCES: Associated Presshttps://apnews.com/47d8e0bf05354260931de08ad9976a37***]]></description>
