      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANSpaceX's Mars-colonizing Big Falcon Rocket spaceflight system will consist of two parts, a spaceship and a rocket booster, standing 118 meters tall at launch, 11 percent taller than their previous design, reports NBC News.Instead of placing six Raptor engines onto the spaceship, SpaceX now plans to add seven Raptor engines to power the BFR spaceship.The spaceship will also now include two movable fins near its nose and two larger fins near its tail. SpaceX's founder and CEO Elon Musk says this will help the vehicle maneuver its way to safe landings.The previous design didn't include any front fins.He also explained the vehicle will land like a skydive rather than an airplane, landing vertically after slowing its descent.Musk said he believes this design might be better than the previous one. He also added it "looks beautiful."RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. The BFR is shown flight system is shown.2. Six Raptor engines are shown being added onto the spacecraft.3. Fins are shown appearing on the spaceship's nose and tail.4. Spacecraft is shown landing vertically.VOICEOVER (in English): "NBC News reports SpaceX's Mars-colonizing Big Falcon Rocket spaceflight system will consist of two parts, a spaceship and a rocket booster, standing 118 meters tall at launch, 11 percent taller than their previous design.""Instead of placing six Raptor engines onto the spaceship, SpaceX now plans to add seven Raptor engines to power the BFR spaceship.""The spaceship will also now include two movable fins near its nose and two larger fins near its tail. SpaceX's founder and CEO Elon Musk says this will help the vehicle maneuver its way to safe landings.""The previous design didn't include any front fins.""He also explained the vehicle will land like a skydive rather than an airplane, landing vertically after slowing its descent."SOURCES: NBC News, Business Insider, Engadget, The Verge, Space.comhttps://www.nbcnews.com/mach/science/how-spacex-s-huge-bfr-spaceship-mars-has-changed-ncna912121https://www.businessinsider.com/elon-musk-spacex-pictures-big-falcon-rocket-spaceship-2018-9https://www.engadget.com/2018/09/21/spacex-mars-base/https://www.theverge.com/2018/9/17/17871724/spacex-big-falcon-rocket-bfr-mars-design-elon-muskhttps://www.space.com/41825-spacex-giant-bfr-rocket-moon-flight-design-art.html***]]></description>
